<P>
SOVIET DEFENSE CHIEF IN U.S. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The first Soviet defense minister to visit the United States arrived in 
Washington for a six-day visit in which he will hold talks with U.S. leaders, 
tour American military bases and take in a Civil War site. Dmitri T. Yazov, 65, 
was greeted on his arrival at Andrews Air Force Base, Md., by Defense 
Undersecretary Paul G. Wolfowitz. Yazov was accompanied by his wife, Emma, and 
senior Soviet military leaders. Yazov's schedule includes visits to Navy and 
Marine Corps installations in Southern California. Defense Secretary Dick 
Cheney issued the invitation to Yazov to reciprocate for the visit Cheney's 
predecessor, Frank C. Carlucci, made to the Soviet Union in August, 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
