<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thousands of supporters of the late dictator Ferdinand E. Marcos marched 
through Manila demanding that President Corazon Aquino allow his body to be 
buried in the Philippines. Meanwhile, Aquino -- who barred the return on 
grounds that this might spark civil disorder -- said on her weekly radio 
program that she will follow any Philippine Supreme Court order to allow the 
return of Marcos' body but is confident the justices will support her ban. 
Attorneys for Marcos said they will file a motion today asking the Supreme 
Court to reconsider its Sept. 15 decision dismissing a petition to allow Marcos 
to come home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
