<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In western Cambodia, heavy fighting continued as the government brought in 
reinforcements to face a drive by non-Communist resistance forces. The 
offensive by the Khmer People's National Liberation Front was launched less 
than a week after Vietnam proclaimed the complete withdrawal of its troops from 
Cambodia. Military sources at the Thai-Cambodian border said the fighting, 
along a 30-mile stretch from 12 miles to 25 inside Cambodia, had forced the 
closure of all border trading points. 
</P>
