<HEADLINE>
<P>
SURGERY EXPECTED FOR HONECKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BONN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
East German leader Erich Honecker, rumored to be suffering from cancer, will 
travel to Switzerland for surgery, a West German newspaper said Sunday in a 
report attributed to Western intelligence services. 
</P>
<P>
The Welt am Sonntag paper said Honecker will travel to Switzerland immediately 
after celebrations Oct. 7 marking the 40th anniversary of the founding of the 
German Democratic Republic (East Germany). The newspaper gave no other details 
about the report but attributed it to Western intelligence sources. 
</P>
<P>
Speculation that Honecker has cancer was fueled in early September when 
security sources in Bonn said he had undergone an unsuccessful gall bladder 
operation. 
</P>
<P>
The 77-year-old leader resumed his duties last week after a five-week absence 
from office, during which he underwent surgery. East German officials rejected 
claims that the operation was not successful and said Honecker was in good 
health. 
</P>
