<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOUNTAIN LION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Wildlife Protection Initiative would indeed prohibit trophy hunting of the 
California mountain lion, but would not restrict hunting of any other species. 
</P>
<P>
In fact, the initiative would protect extensive areas of habitat for a wide 
variety of wildlife, specifically including deer. 
</P>
<P>
The dramatic decline in the numbers of deer in California is largely a 
reflection of habitat loss. This decline can only be stopped if enough deer 
habitat is acquired to protect remaining deer (and mountain lion) populations. 
</P>
<P>
The hunting community should support the initiative, since it offers the only 
real hope that deer habitat will be preserved for generations to come in both 
Northern and Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
Anglers should also support the initiative, since fishing streams throughout 
the state would also be improved. 
</P>
<P>
GERALD H. MERAL 
</P>
<P>
Campaign Manager 
</P>
<P>
California Wildlife 
</P>
<P>
Protection Committee 
</P>
<P>
Sacramento 
</P>
</TEXT>
