<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO BODIES FOUND IN LEUCADIA HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies called to a Leucadia home Sunday morning made a gruesome 
discovery. The decomposing bodies of two family members were found in separate 
parts of the home on Eolus Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
The county coroner's office identified the dead as John Michael Flagg, 46, and 
his mother, Sybil Flagg. 
</P>
<P>
Homicide Sgt. Chuck Curtis said the two may have been dead for more than a 
week. 
</P>
<P>
Another resident of the home, Sally Flagg, sister and daughter of the deceased, 
told homicide detectives that her brother had come home drunk earlier Sunday 
and had tried to break into her room. She was being held for questioning. 
</P>
