<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MISSING MAN'S BODY FOUND IN CASTAIC LAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of a 23-year old Los Angeles man was found Sunday morning in lower 
Castaic Lake, a day after his brother reported him missing, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Miguel Sanchez is believed to have drowned accidentally Saturday afternoon, but 
an autopsy will be conducted, said Lt. Ed Chenal of the Los Angeles County 
Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
Sanchez's brother reported him missing Saturday. Deputies in a helicopter 
spotted the body about 11:30 a.m. Sunday in shallow water in the lower lake, 
Chenal said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
