<P>
CITY WANTS ADDRESSES VISIBLE FROM STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To speed police and fire response times, Huntington Beach officials will start 
enforcing a law requiring homes and businesses to make their addresses visible 
from the street. 
</P>
<P>
"We have a lot of problems with our larger (apartment and industrial) complexes 
in finding the addresses," Fire Department Capt. Tom Huntley said. 
</P>
<P>
City inspectors have the authority to fine building owners for not complying 
with the law, but that probably will not be necessary, Huntley said. 
</P>
