<P>
LABOR PARTY SCRAPS A-ARMS STANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BRIGHTON, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Britain's opposition Labor Party today scrapped its longstanding commitment to 
unilateral nuclear disarmament, handing leader Neil Kinnock a key victory in 
his drive to steer the party on a new moderate course. 
</P>
<P>
A revised defense strategy which abandons a unilateral approach and commits 
Labor to joining global disarmament talks was approved by a 3-2 margin on the 
second day of the party's weeklong annual conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
