<P>
MAN KILLED IN SANTA ANA SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 24-year-old man was shot to death as he stood with friends on a sidewalk in 
Santa Ana in what police today described as a gang-related drive-by shooting. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana Police Sgt. Doyle Smith said today that Gerardo Veloz of Santa Ana 
was fatally wounded by shots fired Sunday night from a passing car while he was 
standing on a sidewalk in the 500 block of South Spruce Street. 
</P>
<P>
Veloz was pronounced dead about 9:30 p.m. No other people were injured, and no 
arrests have been made. Smith said police have only sketchy information about 
the vehicle involved in the shooting. 
