<P>
ACTOR LINKED TO IMELDA MARCOS CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor George Hamilton has been described by federal authorities as an 
unindicted co-conspirator of former Philippine First Lady Imelda Marcos, it was 
reported today. 
</P>
<P>
Hamilton's name appeared on documents filed in U.S. District Court in 
connection with the case against Marcos, according to New York Newsday. 
</P>
<P>
An indictment last October charged that Marcos and her husband, the late 
Philippine President Ferdinand E. Marcos, stole $168 million from the 
Philippine treasury. 
</P>
<P>
Also named were Manhattan real estate developers Joseph and Ralph Bernstein, 
who are brothers, and the Marcos children, Irene, Imee and Ferdinand Jr., the 
newspaper said. 
</P>
<P>
The list of unindicted co-conspirators was included in a pretrial motion filed 
by one of Marcos' co-defendants, California Overseas Bank. 
</P>
<P>
The actor, known for his perpetual tan and for his portrayal of a vampire in 
the movie "Love at First Bite," has denied rumors that he and Marcos were 
romantically linked. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, George Hamilton 
</P>
