<TEXT>
<P>
International Business Machines Corp. today said it has offered employees at 
four locations voluntary separation in a continuing cost reduction effort 
unrelated to last week's announcement of lower earnings. 
</P>
<P>
"We expect 600 to 1,000 to elect to retire or resign from the business," a 
spokesman for the computer giant said. 
